Title: Great idea, less than stellar delivery.
Text: While I love the idea of this, the actual product just isn't there yet. The charge didn't last long enough to get my hair done (I do have long and thick hair) so YMMV but the second time I tried to use it, it seems that the charge didn't even last as long as the first. Too much trouble for me. I was hoping for a true rechargeable product which would be excellent--if only this one delivered.

Title: Too big to hold comfortably.
Text: I like that this is cordless amd portable but it‚Äôs hard to hold and use because the iron is so wide and thick.

Title: Great selection of implements.
Text: This is a complete set for doing manicures or pedicures and even a couple for extra things like maybe for your face. All the tools are strong amd sturdy. The case unfortunately is not as strong. The straps that hold the implements in the case  are weak and thin and one broke right away. Overall a good set they definitely thought of everything to include in the kit.

Title: Likeable liquid lipstick
Text:
To me the shade on the product picture looks like it might have a little pink in it but I don't notice it when I apply it. Maybe that's just me ü§î Regardless, I feel the shade is very pretty...and definitely is metallic.

It's also very long-lasting- to the point that later when taking it off, I used both an oil cleanser and makeup remover. Transferring is minimal. It actually stays a little sticky the whole time while wearing it, so that makes it a little surprising that it's so long lasting- since many liquids dry completely. It's not overly sticky, so I didn't find it bothersome.

Applies smoothly- it does feel like a velvety, whipped texture

If you're concerned about the appearance of lines on your lips with a liquid lipstick- I feel this is one makes them a bit pronounced.

Overall, for a liquid lipstick, I think it's pretty good. Has rich pigment and has a stand-out metallic look

Packaging is pretty

Title: Liking it
Text: The skin on my neck has lost a lot of elasticity. I wouldn't say it's in bad shape but I feel it is for being in mid 30s. Having health stuff going on, former daily tanning machine user, former smoker and my weight goes up-and-down- all things that have contributed to my skin changes and my neck is no exception. This cream is soothing and leaves a lot of moisturize but not a lot of goop. I feel like my skin looks smoother, though I'm sure more consistent and long-term use will bring the most benefits and results. The texture of it is so creamy and thick and feels great on! Arrived sealed and packaged-up really well.

Title: Moisturizing But No Firming
Text: This cream feels great on my skin and is readily absorbed but I have been using it for months now and haven't seen any "firming" effect. For the current price it's too high for what it does - which is being an effective moisturizer. There are many products out there that hydrate your skin - I usually prefer olive oil-based products. This one doesn't change the sagginess around my neck so only three stars from me!

Title: Use Insted of Foundation
Text: I am an Octogenarian and makeup in the form of foundation looks silly on me and only serves to make me look older. This sheer balm in a compact balm gives my face a soft natural glow instead of a caked surface. I then apply blush and eyeliner, eyeshadow, eyebrows and a very sheer lipstick. I love the balm and the presentation of the product.

Title: Bold glimmer eyeshadow
Text: This is a very funky fun collection of glitter eyeshadow. This is for those who want to add a lot of glamour to their makeup and are bold, young and fashion forward. In these days of mask wearing, why not make a statement with your eyes since your lips are hidden?

Title: Moisturizes, Comforts, Some Color Correction-Emphasizes My Pores, Need An Ingredient List
Text:
JUNGSAEMMOOL Minifying Cica Mist Balm is a moisturizing balm for sensitive skin that soothes irritation and helps redness. It‚Äôs described as having green calamine to tone down redness and cica pine water to calm skin. But I‚Äôm unable to find a full ingredient list. The box has directions in English but lacks an ingredient list in English, so I don‚Äôt know what‚Äôs even in this product. I have dry, sensitive skin and avoid many skincare ingredients, so I won‚Äôt make this balm or any product part of my daily routine without an ingredient list.

I have used this balm a few times after my moisturizer and before foundation (if wearing makeup). The balm smells light and pleasant, and it adds some comforting moisture. While it tends to sink into my skin, I do get some color correction of redness on my nose and cheeks. But it‚Äôs less than I get with my corrective color makeup. If the balm has healthy ingredients that benefit my skin while also correcting some degree of redness, I‚Äôd likely prefer it to just hiding redness with makeup. But I can‚Äôt judge if the trade off is there without knowing ingredients.

This balm also makes my skin smoother. It feels like it might have silicone and/or glycerin and feels a lot like a primer under my makeup. I like the moist and spreadable texture, except it‚Äôs so soft I can‚Äôt just swipe across the top with the puff for an even amount of product as it smooshes in the balm and gouges out pieces (which I then spread and dab with the puff). It becomes less noticeable as the balm soaks in, but I don‚Äôt like that this settles into and emphasizes pores on my nose. This is just okay for me. 3 stars. Made in Korea.

Title: Pretty Metallic Looks More Bronze Than Rose, Sticky Formula, Feels Drying, Best w/ Gloss Over It
Text:
This Beauty Bakerie Lip Whip Liquid Metallic Lipstick in Ros√© Pos√© comes in a cute tube and is a pretty metallic color lipstick that spreads on with a sponge type wand. The color reads darker on me than I‚Äôd expect from the photo, but it‚Äôs a lovely metallic shade that looks like a bronze with rose hue or a little rose gold in it. I have light skin with an olive hue and rosy color lips, and this color is flattering but is probably even better on medium and dark skin tones.

But, while this lipstick initially spreads on smooth and velvety, it stays sticky and doesn‚Äôt fully dry down on me even with just one application. It doesn‚Äôt feel comfortable as I tend to get dry lips and it adds no moisture (and may be drying my lips more). Used alone, it accentuates lines and flakiness even used after a great lip scrub. And it doesn‚Äôt work applied over a little lip balm as it rolls off in weird little pieces. For me, it‚Äôs best with a little gloss over it, but it still feels sticky and rolls off (to a lesser extent) if I rub my lips together. Overall, it‚Äôs just okay at best. 3 stars.

Title: Light
Text: This is a great moisturizer. It goes on light and doesn‚Äôt make my skin feel sticky. It absorbs quickly and my skin is dewy and moist.

Title: Nice Shade But Sticky Texture (B- Grade)
Text:
The lipstick is a nice color and shade but it is a bit on the sticky side so the texture may not feel right for some people. It also doesn't last as long as you expect and not so smudge proof, which is surprising when you look at the price.

Katiebabs

Title: MOISTURIZING GIVES LIGHT VEIL OF COLOR WITH A MATTE FINISH
Text:
This is another interesting Korean skincare product. The description and images leaves the impression that this is a powder product, in reality, the texture is closer to ELF's putty primer. When I applied it to dry bare skin using the puff it pilled slightly, I did get better results blending it with my finger tips. It leaves an overall light green veil of color on bare skin that's not overly noticeable and leaves a matte finish. Don't let the matte finish fool you though, it melts into your skin leaving it moisturized without feeling greasy.

My skin is only slightly sensitive and when irritated doesn't react with major noticeable redness or heat. It did calm the redness I sometimes have around my nose and chin. I've not yet tested this over or under foundation and wonder if it would work well as a primer? More information regarding the benefits, ingredients and use are on the company's site.

Title: Great setting
Text: Works well

Title: Delicious flavors
Text: Sweet and colorful

Title: Not pigmented and stays wet
Text: For $20, these eyeshadow sticks are $5 a pop. I expected a better quality shadow but it‚Äôs not impressive to me. The shadow is very runny and there is no pigment once it blends in. It stays wet on my eyelid which I didn‚Äôt like at all. I was expecting a higher pigment from the advertised photos as well but it‚Äôs just glitter once it‚Äôs smoothed out.

Title: Reliable
Text: These little bottles are a great size and shape. They are reasonable to fill, and the lids close securely. All of the spray pumps have worked without any issue.

Title: Reliable Tools
Text: This case, and all the tools inside are very sturdy and reliable. The sharp parts are sharp, and the moving parts move easily.

Title: Moisturizing face powder\balm!
Text:
I'm half Korean and have been using Korean skincare for 30 years. This product is not for sale at my local Asian store as of August 2022. I assume it is authentic, but I have no way to confirm.

I was pleasantly surprised at how well it blended with my foundation and how light it felt. It can be used under your foundation or over and looks great either way. It is a nice quality powder that I will be incorporating into my make up routine.I wear this powder over I use as the last step in my make-up routine. Its a great finish it last for hours and looks great. I have brown eyes and medium olive skin. It does not irritate my sensitive skin, either.

Hope you found this review helpful!

Title: Perfect for My COVID Cleaning :-)
Text:
In these COVID times, we've had shortages of some basic cleaning and health items. I started reading some blogs about how to make some easy cleansers with natural products, like castile soap. Since then, I've been whipping up cleaning solutions like I'm trying to earn a Ph.D. in Potions from Hogwarts :-).

These sprays are a good easy size to hold and carry without cramping or hurting hand with the weight of liquid. Not huge like some cleaning bottle sprayers. The nozzles can be turned from mist to stream and everything in between. The tube reaches to the bottom, so there is less waste. The bottles are clear so you can fill them and monitor them easily.

These probably won't last a lifetime, but I'm happy with them. Better than reusing old chemical-laden bottles when trying to go greener.

Hope you found this review helpful!

Title: Color is inaccurate

Title: Fun for yourself or as a gift
Text: These are really nice and create a sheer shimmery lightly colored eyeshadow. With a good primer or doesn't crease. Without primer, it creases.

Title: Have to my husband as a gift.
Text: It's great for travel and for home. Smells sexy. Perfect little kit to try these products out. If you like the smaller size, then you can purchase large sizes.

Title: Nice lightweight magnetic lashes.
Text: Easy to use and wear. Slightly itchy, but not too much compared to some of the cheap ones out there and the glue ones. I like that you get a different style in each set. You can change it up from natural to dramatic whenever you want. Getting more options for your money, great idea!

Title: So soft!
Text: These eyelashes are so soft! I love them, and the variety of styles is great too, some are more casual, perfect for a daily use, others are more extreme and definitely only for date nights or nights out. I highly recommend this, you'll have a pair of lashes for any scenario!

Title: Love the color. Long-Lasting. Need one coat.
Text:
I like this Rose Pose liquid lip color. It is a light rosy tan metallic shade.
It is long-lasting and I did a paper test soon after applying it and it did not stain the paper, at all.
I really like that a little goes a long way. I only need to apply one light coat to give me the shade I want.
Overall, I really like this lip color. I like the fun packaging and the whole bakery theme.

Title: Reduced redness & hydrating, but need ingredient list in ENGLISH!
Text:
This comes in a nice outer product box. Made in Korea. The brand‚Äôs website said it‚Äôs 100% vegan, excluding animal ingredients and animal experiments. It also doesn‚Äôt include parabens.

It comes in a nice compact. It‚Äôs a compact like a cushion foundation where you open it and there‚Äôs a kind of lid that holds the sponge applicator, and you lift that lid to reveal the product. You press the applicator sponge into it (or your own sponge or brush) and then apply it. The brand‚Äôs website said the included sponge applicator is an ‚Äúeco puff‚Äù made of ‚Äúeco-friendly corns‚Äù and is ‚Äú99.9% anti-bacterial and water-repellent,‚Äù which makes it safe on skin and keeps puff clean.

This is a liquidy but balm kind of texture. It isn‚Äôt as thick as a balm. It just feels like a cushion foundation. But this isn‚Äôt a foundation. It has a very light, mint green color to it. It‚Äôs so light that it‚Äôs almost white but has the green color to it. When applied, it reduces redness. It doesn‚Äôt do as well as my more pigmented green correctors, but it does a nice job while being hydrating and lightweight on the skin. It‚Äôs something that works well before applying foundation. It is lightweight enough to wear well under foundation. It isn‚Äôt a primer really, it doesn‚Äôt smooth out the skin or fill in pores. But, it does reduce the redness in my skin so then I use less foundation and concealer. If you have a TON of redness or it‚Äôs REALLY red, this might not be enough since it isn‚Äôt extremely pigmented. But, it will make a difference. I like it isn‚Äôt drying on the skin either.

I‚Äôm just not sure how I feel about it though. It works well on the skin. But, I do like to know what‚Äôs in my products. I don‚Äôt like that they provided barely any product info, and the ingredients on the product box weren‚Äôt in English. They also didn‚Äôt include them here on the product page. Not even the product photos provided any real info on the product - what it does, who it‚Äôs for, how to use it, ingredients, etc. I had to go to the brand‚Äôs website to find out more. Yes, it‚Äôs a simple Google search, but it‚Äôs not really something you should have to do.

Normally, I would just go to the brand‚Äôs website to find the list of ingredients when they‚Äôre not included on the Amazon product page. But, the Jung Saem Mool website didn‚Äôt have them on their website either. I looked for them elsewhere and did find an ingredient list on Korean Beauty Box, but didn‚Äôt think they were accurate because they didn‚Äôt include centella asiatica, pine sprout, or green calamine powder, which are supposed to be in this product. So, I translated the ingredients from the box myself. But, I‚Äôm not that confident in the ingredients provided on the box.(I included a photo from the box, and also included the ingredients at the end of my review in English)

It doesn‚Äôt seem like a complete list of ingredients to me. It has the first ingredient as titanium dioxide. It has tocopherol (vitamin E) as the 3rd ingredient. The rest of the ingredient are 7, kind of versions I‚Äôd guess you‚Äôd call them, of centella asiatica. There‚Äôs nothing else listed. It‚Äôs kind of odd. The brand‚Äôs website said this is supposed to have ‚Äú2 plants - pine sprout containing fresh moisture and centella asiatica roots.‚Äù I saw the ‚Äúcentella asiatica roots‚Äù in the ingredients when I translated them. But didn‚Äôt see any ‚Äúpine sprout.‚Äù I also saw something about ‚Äúcica pine water‚Äù on the brand‚Äôs website, but again, not sure what that‚Äôs supposed to be? The brand‚Äôs website also mentioned ‚ÄúNatural green calamine powder covers reddened skin tone.‚Äù Again, I didn‚Äôt see any calamine powder at all in the ingredients.

The 7, I guess versions, of Centella Asiatica are:
Centella Asiatica Extract (5,159,235ppm) - Well known soothing, antioxidant, and moisturizing ingredient. Anti-inflammatory. The main biologically active components are Asiaticoside, madecassoside, asiatic acid, and madecassic acid. All of which are in this.

Centella Asiatica Leaf Extract (0.035ppm)

Centella Asiatica Root Extract (0.03ppm)

Madecassoside (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica.

Madecassic Acid (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica.

Asiaticoside (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica.

Asiatic Acid (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica. It‚Äôs less prominent than it‚Äôs sister component, Asiaticoside, but it still contributes to the well-established moisturizing and wound healing abilities of Centella Asiatica.

Overall, it works well. It reduces my redness, feels hydrating on the skin, and works well on its own and under foundation. It feels lightweight on the skin. If they provided the full ingredient list, it would be something I‚Äôd be willing to purchase. But, right now, I don‚Äôt like they didn‚Äôt include them and don‚Äôt like that they can‚Äôt even be found online as far as I could tell. And I just have a hard time believing the ingredient list I translated from the box is the full ingredient list. I don‚Äôt know. If the ingredients aren‚Äôt a big factor for you, this is nice and works well. If knowing the ingredients are important to you, I‚Äôd look elsewhere. There‚Äôs other similar products that actually provide a full ingredient list, and a lot of them are far cheaper. I give it 3 stars.

How to Use (from brand‚Äôs website):
Use as last step of skin care routine. Dip puff into content and gently apply and dab on skin.

Special Tips (from brand‚Äôs website)
Carry it in makeup bag or purse for easy supply of moisture to skin when it dries up.
Use as lightweight skin tone corrector to correct sensitive skin tone covered by masks instead of applying heavy, caking makeup.

FULL INGREDIENTS
Ingredients | Titanium dioxide (CI 77891], Centella Asiatica Extract (5,159,235ppm), Tocopherol, Centella Asiatica Leaf Extract (0.035ppm), Centella Asiatica Root Extract (0.03ppm), Madecassoside (0.0025ppm), Madecassic Acid (0.0025ppm), Asiaticoside (0.0025ppm), Asiatic Acid (0.0025ppm)

**NOTE: Just for reference, 1ppm = 0.0001% (or 10,000 ppm = 1%). So‚Ä¶

Centella Asiatica Extract (5,159,235ppm) = 515.9235%
*5,159,235ppm is parts per million, so it means there‚Äôs 5,159,235 parts of Centella Asiatica in one million molecules
Centella Asiatica Leaf Extract (0.035ppm) = 0.0000035%
Centella Asiatica Root Extract (0.03ppm) = 0.000003%
Madecassoside (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%
Madecassic Acid (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%
Asiaticoside (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%
Asiatic Acid (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%

Title: 2 of 3 have micro glitter (mica). Sticky but not too bad. Moisturizing
Text:
These come in a nice little box. They are vegan and cruelty free. They are made in the USA. I included the ingredients at the end of my review.

You get 3 glosses - a peachy pink toned one that has a strawberry scent/flavor, a more reddish toned one that has a grape scent/flavor, and a clear one that has a bubble gum scent/flavor. As for the scents, I can notice them when applying, not so much after the fact. I don‚Äôt really notice a taste really with any of them, but the ingredients do list ‚Äúflavor‚Äù not fragrance/parfum, so it made me think they‚Äôd have more taste to them. Not a big deal to me though.

While 2 of them are tinted in color, the color doesn‚Äôt really translate onto the lips. They just look clear on the lips. They don‚Äôt change any color of lip liner, lipstick, matte lip, etc. that I put them over top of. So, I liked that.

The formula is nice. It feels nice and moisturizing on the lips, which I expected given they have nice moisturizing ingredients like Shea butter, coconut oil, and squalane. They do feel SLIGHTLY sticky on the lips. I hate sticky glosses, but these aren‚Äôt overly sticky. They don‚Äôt feel thick or heavy on the lips. They feel nice and thin. They are glosses so they do need re-applied often throughout the day. But, I‚Äôm used to that with glosses so it‚Äôs not a big deal to me.

The strawberry and grape both have micro glitter in them (mica). I didn‚Äôt know that when I got these. None of the product photos showed they had glitter and the description didn‚Äôt say it either. I‚Äôm not a fan of micro glitter in my lip glosses. I feel once the gloss wears off, it usually leaves behind glitter particles on my lips. Also, they can sometimes feel gritty. So, I was surprised when I saw 2 of the 3 had glitter. Luckily, these didn‚Äôt feel gritty. I do notice that there are some glitter particles on my lips after they wear off, but it‚Äôs not too bad. The glitter particles are really small, so it‚Äôs not really noticeable. So, I don‚Äôt mind that.

Overall, these are nice glosses with a nice formula. They might seem pricey when seeing the $30 price tag, but you‚Äôre getting 3 tubes of glosses, so that‚Äôs only $10 a piece, which isn‚Äôt bad. Of course, it isn‚Äôt great. You can get a tube of gloss that looks great and works just as well from the drugstore for slightly less. But, the ingredients might make it worth it to spend the little more. I give them 4 stars.

INGREDIENTS
Bubblegum Lip Glossy:
Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Oil*, Isododecane, Ethylene/Propylene/Styrene Copolymer, Flavor, Sorbitan Oleate, Squalane, Butylene/Ethylene/Styrene Copolymer, Tocopherol, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter Extract, Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E Acetate).

*Organic/Biologique.

Grape Lip Glossy:
Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Oil*, Isododecane, Ethylene/Propylene/Styrene Copolymer, Flavor, Sorbitan Oleate, Squalane, Butylene/Ethylene/Styrene Copolymer, Tocopherol, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter Extract, Mica, Titanium Dioxide, Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E Acetate), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Red 33 (CI#17200), CI 15850 (Red 7), Iron Oxides (CI 77499).

*Organic/Biologique.

Strawberry Lip Glossy:
Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Cocos Nucifera (Coconut) Oil*, Isododecane, Ethylene/Propylene/Styrene Copolymer, Flavor, Sorbitan Oleate, Squalane, Butylene/Ethylene/Styrene Copolymer, Tocopherol, Titanium Dioxide, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter Extract, Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Mica, Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E Acetate), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Red 27 Lake (CI 45410), Silica, Tin Oxide.

*Organic/Biologique

Title: Gorgeous!! Such A Great Set!
Text:
[[VIDEOID:a7c1d14af37e75840e647b8774b319cb]] I have been wanting to get a variety of different liquid glitter eyeshadows, but I kept only finding them where you have to buy them individually. I was happy to see this set of 4!

These liquid glitter eyeshadows are GORGEOUS!

They come in a product box. The tubes of product have gold caps and clear tubes, so you can see the shade. The brand name and logo is on the front of the tubes in gold. The applicator is a nice sized doe foot - not too big for my small eyes, but big enough. These are short tubes, so the applicator is short. But, it‚Äôs still easy to hold and maneuver. The shade number and name are on a sticker on the bottom of the tube.

You get 4
- 001 Mauve Plum - Mauve liquid shadow with silver glitter.
- 002 Rosy Gold - Rose gold liquid shadow with silver glitter.
- 003 Silver Flash - White liquid shadow with silver glitter
- 004 Sparkle Midnight - Black liquid shadow with silver glitter.

They all look so beautiful. The shimmer with them looks even with application. You can layer them well. They don‚Äôt take too long to dry. They lasted well on my hooded eyes without creasing (that is, no more than what I normally get with any eyeshadow). When the light hits these they look so beautiful.

I show photos of swatches - I did 1 swipe for each color. Then I did little areas where I layered the colors to show how they built up. I also did a video showing them.

I think this is such a great set! To get 4 liquid glitter shadows for $13.99 (at the time of writing this review), I think that‚Äôs a great deal! All other liquid glitter shadows I‚Äôve found were sold individually and buying 4 would have been way more than this set costs! I‚Äôm definitely going to be using these up and hoping they‚Äôll come out with additional colors soon!!
